_TOOL_NAME_
----------------
This utility manipulates squashfs filesystems.
To create a filesystem image use:

  _TOOL_NAME_ <fs_dir> <fs_image_file> <max_size>
  
where:
    <fs_dir> - directory which contents will form a filesystem, 
		will become a root directory
    <fs_image_file> - filename of the filesystem image

  Example:

    # ./_TOOL_NAME_ rootfs/ rootfs.img

The utility can also be used to decompress an existing filesystem
image:

  _TOOL_NAME_ -u <fs_image_file> <fs_dir>
  
where:
    <fs_image_file> - filename of the existing filesystem image
    <fs_dir> - directory where image will be decompressed
    
  Example:
  
    # ./_TOOL_NAME_ -u ROOTFS.img root_fs/
    

